cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CL

This paper deals with unsupervised domain adaptation for spatially-structured prediction tasks, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework involves regularization strategies and adversarial training, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of a cross-task distillation module, which suggests a potential connection to robotics (cs.RO) where multi-task learning is often used. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (cs.CL) in the sense that it proposes a novel regularization strategy called Contour-based content regularization (CCR), which involves analyzing the structure of images.
